page.title: 09HOUSING DUNLOP
page.content: THERE ARE A VARIETY OF HOUSES IN DUNLOP,RANGING FROM HOUSES 100 YEARS OLD TO THE VERY LATEST BUNGALOWS. DUNLOP HAD 161 COUNCIL HOUSES BUT THERE ARE ONLY 157 BECAUSE 4 ARE NOW OWNER-OCCUPIED.THE NEWEST COUNCIL HOUSES ARE ABOUT 11 YEARS OLD. THERE ARE THIRTY-SEVEN TRADITIONAL ; TWO UP- TWO DOWN,HOUSES IN DUNLOP. THESE ARE SITUATED IN THE CONSERVATION AREA OF THE VILLAGE.MOST OF THESE HOUSES ARE AROUND ONE HUNDRED YEARS OLD. THERE ARE SEVEN PRIVATE HOUSES IN DAM PARK , FOUR BUNGALOWS AND ONE DETATCHED VILLA AT WOODSIDE.THE PREVIOUS OWNERS OF DAM PARK LIVE IN AN OLDER HOUSE AT THE TOP OF WOODSIDE. THERE IS UNLIKELY TO BE FURTHER HOUSING DEVELOPMENT IN THE VILLAGE BECAUSE OF THE SEWAGE PROBLEM.
